children.text: 1. What is the market potential for plant-based meat in the next 5 years?
- Mckinsey . May 14, 2020 . 8 min read . News
The Booming Future of Plant-Based Meat

The market potential for plant-based meat in the next 5 years is significant. By 2030, cultivated meat could provide as much as a half of 1 percent of the world's meat supply, which amounts to billions of pounds. This indicates a growing demand for plant-based alternatives to traditional meat products.
The market potential for plant-based meat in the next 5 years will depend on several key factors. These include consumer acceptance, addressing

concerns about health and safety, job implications, and economic effects, cost competitiveness compared to conventional meat, policy responses from countries and regions, and the ability to scale up production to achieve economies of scale..
